[h1]Blockades[/h1]
Adds a [b]Blockade[/b] default behavior. Ships hold a hemisphere formation on the hostile side of a target gate and engage transiting hostiles. AI factions at war auto-deploy blockade fleets at gates leading from enemy claimspace into their own.

Built for X4: Foundations 9.0. Pure additions — no vanilla files modified, compatible with everything.

[b]⚠ Work-in-progress.[/b] Player-led blockades and the AI auto-deploy flow are stable in short play sessions; long-running balance, edge cases (sub re-targeting after gate switches, behavior across sector handoffs), and very large fleets still need testing in the wild. [b]Please report bugs[/b] — log snippets help most. See [b]Source, issues, and license[/b] below for where to file.

[h2]Player usage[/h2]
[olist]
[*]Select a ship or wing.
[*]Open the Behavior dropdown.
[*]Pick [b]Blockade[/b].
[*]Choose a gate as the target.
[/olist]

The leader sits at slot 0 in front of the gate (offset slightly above the highway centerline so XL/L ships don't fight transiting mass traffic). Subordinates fill an inner ring (theta=30°) closer to the gate, an outer ring (60°) further out, and a flat ring (80°) beyond. Ships are sorted by class — L/XL inner, M middle, S/lighter outer — so capitals anchor and fast hulls intercept.

When any enemy ship enters [b]Engagement Range[/b] of the gate (or the leader), all subordinates dispatch to engage. After the area clears they fall back to their slots. The leader is bastion-style: holds position, fires its turrets at anything in range. L/XL forward main batteries don't auto-fire under the Blockade order (vanilla X4 limitation) — turrets handle leader-side engagement.

[h2]Recommended leader[/h2]
Use an [b]L (destroyer)[/b] or [b]M (frigate / corvette)[/b] as the wing leader. [b]XL pathfinding currently has issues[/b] — XL hulls work fine as subordinates.

[h2]Order parameters[/h2]
[list]
[*][b]Distance from Gate[/b] (default 6 km) — radius of the formation sphere.
[*][b]Engagement Range[/b] (default ship's radar range) — hostiles outside this are ignored.
[*][b]Pursue Targets[/b] (advanced) — if on, ships chase beyond the formation.
[*][b]Face Away From Gate[/b] — reverse the formation's lookat for sector-side blockades.
[*][b]Side[/b] (auto) — 0 picks side from gate type; 1 = destination-facing; -1 = interior-facing.
[*][b]Timeout[/b] (default 0 = infinite).
[/list]

[h2]AI auto-blockade[/h2]
Every 30 minutes (configurable), the mod walks every active gate in the galaxy and looks at the sector owner on each side. If the two owners are actively hostile (relation ≤ -0.25 and the engine flags them as may-attack) and both are real claimspace factions (Xenon, Khaak, Yaki, Scaleplate, Civilian/Criminal/Smuggler/Visitor sub-factions, and the player are skipped), the sector-side owner — the [i]defender[/i] — is considered as a possible blockade owner.

If the defender has at least one shipyard, no blockade fleet (ours or anyone else's, including the player's, within 25 km of the gate) is already on this gate, [b]and we haven't already dispatched a blockade there in a prior tick[/b], the mod spawns a small force at that shipyard: by default [b]1 destroyer + 3 frigates + 4 fighters[/b], race-matched to the defender (Argon, Paranid, Teladi, Split, Terran, Boron, falling back to Argon for unknown races). Each of those ships is independently assigned the [b]Blockade[/b] order with its own slot index, so the group ends up arranged in the same hemisphere formation the player would see — but as peers running the order, not under a wing leader.

A logbook entry under the News category announces the deployment. The mod re-checks each active blockade every 30 minutes and disbands it (cancels the Blockade order on surviving ships, removes the bookkeeping entry, and writes a disband log entry) when any of the following becomes true: the gate or its destination no longer exists, the destination sector flipped to the defender's faction (war was won), relation between the two has thawed (> -0.1), or all ships in the fleet have been destroyed.

[h2]Compatibility[/h2]
[list]
[*][b]X4 9.0+[/b]
[*]All Egosoft DLCs supported.
[*][b]No vanilla diffs[/b] — order definition is a new file, no xpath patches.
[*]Removing the mod mid-save leaves spawned ships with an invalid order; they fall back to their previous default behavior.
[/list]

